    "Html": "<p>Hi Boris,</p>\r\n<p>Nice to see that you started using Prism Region Navigation Quickstart. Based on my understanding, you have created a new module (SchedulerModule), but your application is not able to load this. So, this causes that the Intialize method, located in the Module Initializer class, will not be called. So I think that you can find interesting the following forum thread where user reported a similar scenario:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"View.aspx?ThreadId=221865\"><span>Problems loading ModuleCatalog from XAML</span></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Please, take into account that in the aforementioned thread the user  tried to load its module on demand, so you could avoid the step 3 over  there.</p>\r\n<p>Hope this helps.</p>\r\n<p>Fernando Antivero <br><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/fantivero\">http://blogs.southworks.net/fantivero</a></p>",
